olume are organized into four genres-elegies, heroic poems, religious poems, and wisdom poetry. Raffel's new translations include more than twenty poem-riddles, with proposed solutions in a separate section. Prose translations-grouped in historical, testamentary and legal, religious, social and instructional, and medical and magical categories-feature writings by King Alfred, Aelfric, and Wulfstan, among others.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAnglo-SaxonsvLiterary collections. 0aAnglo-SaxonsxLiterary collections. 0aEnglish literaturexModernized versionsxOld English, ca. 450-1100. 0aEnglish literatureyOld English, ca. 450-1100vModernized versions. 0aMiddle AgesvLiterary collections. 0aMiddle AgesxLiterary collections. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh1 aOlsen, Alexandra H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRaffel, Burton08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300130416423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300130416.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles